{
  "_readme": [
    "Curated input for `make seed-models` (scripts/seed-models.mjs). This file is the",
    "anti-clutter mechanism: Pioneer alone returns ~95 models including embeddings and",
    "Gemma/Llama variants. Only what is listed here reaches core.model_library.",
    "",
    "Scope rule: current flagship plus at most one or two tiers down. A model that a",
    "provider has superseded comes out on the next curation pass — this is not an archive.",
    "",
    "Two provider shapes:",
    "  source=api     the provider publishes machine-readable pricing; `models` lists",
    "                 only the ids to keep and rates are pulled live at run time.",
    "  source=manual  no machine-readable feed; rates live here, hand-verified against",
    "                 source_url on verified_at. The script warns when these go stale.",
    "",
    "Rates are USD per 1,000,000 tokens; the script converts to nanos (x 1e9) for",
    "core.model_library. `cached_input` is the cache-READ price, never cache-write.",
    "Where a provider publishes no cache discount, cached_input equals input on purpose",
    "— a 0 there would silently zero-rate cached reads.",
    "",
    "Providers are keyed on nullclaw's canonical identifiers (post alias-map, see",
    "oss/nullclaw/src/provider_names.zig): `kimi` not moonshot-cn, `xai` not grok.",
    "",
    "!! base_url is LOAD-BEARING, never decorative. Three of our provider names collide",
    "!! with a nullclaw alias that resolves to a DIFFERENT endpoint than the one priced",
    "!! here (see nullclaw_alias_collisions below). We always ship base_url explicitly,",
    "!! so nullclaw's default table is never consulted. Do not 'simplify' by dropping it:",
    "!! the failure is silent — right price, wrong continent.",
    "",
    "Deliberately absent: nvidia-nim (no per-token pricing exists — credits retired",
    "Sep 2025, production needs an AI Enterprise licence)."
  ],
  "verified_at": "2026-07-19",
  "stale_after_days": 45,

  "nullclaw_alias_collisions": {
    "_readme": [
      "Provider names where OUR base_url deliberately differs from what nullclaw's",
      "same-named alias would resolve to. Harmless while base_url is always shipped;",
      "a silent wrong-endpoint bug the moment it is not.",
      "Source: oss/nullclaw/src/providers/factory.zig compat_providers table."
    ],
    "kimi": {
      "ours": "https://api.moonshot.ai/v1",
      "nullclaw_alias_resolves_to": "https://api.moonshot.cn/v1",
      "nullclaw_alias_that_matches_ours": "kimi-intl / moonshot-intl",
      "why_kept": "`kimi` is the name users recognise; the CN/intl split is nullclaw's internal concern and should not leak into our provider dropdown."
    },
    "qwen": {
      "ours": "https://dashscope-intl.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1",
      "nullclaw_alias_resolves_to": "https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1",
      "nullclaw_alias_that_matches_ours": "qwen-intl / dashscope-intl",
      "why_kept": "Same reasoning as kimi."
    }
  },

  "tiering_note": [
    "core.model_library holds ONE rate triple per (provider, model_id), but some models",
    "double their rate above a context threshold, charging the higher rate on ALL tokens",
    "in the request. Those rows carry \"tier\": \"upper\" and are seeded at the HIGHER rate.",
    "Rationale: a coding agent on a real repo crosses 200k routinely, so the upper tier is",
    "the modal case, not the edge case. Under-billing is silent and unrecoverable;",
    "over-billing is visible and refundable. Remove the upper-tier seeding once the schema",
    "grows a tier column."
  ],

